column2: the interior looks like a greasy spoon transported from the shoreline in San Francisco to the center of Houston
column3: but the food options etched on the wall made this odd juxtaposition worth it.  My companion and I both opted for the green eggs -- individual dishes -- and split the season pancake
column6: artichoke hearts and spinach had just the right amount of cheesiness and crunch.  The side of potatoes was crunchy and well-seasoned
